Author: ANGAS
Vol / Page: 1/274
Edition:
Quote: The women's limbs were anointed with <i>kokowai</i>, or red ochre and grease, to protect them from the attacks of the <i>namu</i>, a small species of sand-fly, the bite of which is peculiarly venemous and irritating. <i>Ibid.</i>  1/327  [Kokowai], mixed with oil, is also rubbed over the arms and legs to protect them from the merciless attacks of the <i>namu</i>, or sand-fly.
